REMINGTON RAND, Inc., v. ACME CARD SYSTEM COMPANY and LeRoy A. Franklin. No. 8060. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Oct. 11, 1939. Bean, Brooks, Buckley & Bean, of Buffalo, N. Y., and Allen & Allen, of Cincinnati, Ohio, for appellant. William F. Hall, of Washington, D. C., Lee J. Gary, of Chicago, Ill., and Wood & Wood, of Cincinnati, Ohio, for appellees.

Before PUCKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

*1015PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the appeal herein, 29 F.Supp. 192, be and the same is dismissed pursuant to stipulation of counsel.
